Project.Title: Discovery of glycoprotein biomarker candidates for lung cancer
Project.Description: Glycoproteomics Approach for Identifying Glycobiomarker Candidate Molecules for Tissue Type Classification of Non-small Cell Lung Carcinoma (Hirao et al., JPR 2014, PMID: 25244057). Re-searched original MS2 data using the latest database (UniprotKB) in 2017.

Relation.Keywords: cancer cell line, lectin, IGOT, biomarker, lung cancer

Fractionation.title: AAL-bound glycopeptide
Fractionation.peptide: Glycopeptides captured with a lectin AAL column
Fractionation.note: Tryptic digest of S-reduced and alkylated proteins was applied to AAL column at room temperature or 4 degree C. After washing, glycpeptides were eluted with 5 mM fucose. The glycopeptides were treated with PNGase in oxigen-18-labeled water.

Enzyme_Mod.title: Glycopeptide treated with PNGase in H2_18O

Fractionation.title: ConA-bound glycopeptides
Fractionation.peptide: Glycopeptide captured with a lectin ConA column
Fractionation.note: Tryptic digest of sample was applied to AAL column. The through fraction was reloaded to HHL column. The through fraction was reloaded to a lectin Con A column. After washing, glycopeptides were eluted with 0.2 or 0.5 M methyl mannoside. The glycopeptides were treated with PNGase in oxigen-18-labeled water.

Enzyme_Mod.title: Glycopeptide treated with PNGase in H2_18O

Fractionation.title: HHL-bound glycopeptides

Fractionation.note: Tryptic digest of medium proteins was applied to a lectin AAL-column, then, the through fraction was applied to a lectin HHL-column. After washing, glycopeptides were eluted with 0.2 M methyl mannoside. The glycopeptides were treated with PNGase in oxigen-18-labeled water.
